One man has been killed and several others injured on Wednesday evening when a goods and passenger train collided on the tracks near Bonny Doone Road in Horizon View, West of Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Metrorail services between Randfontein and Roodepoort have been suspended following a crash on Wednesday night that left one person dead. The line will only be up and running again on Saturday. READ: Four detained for burning Braamfontein trains A goods train and a passenger train collided in Horizon View, West of Johannesburg on Wednesday night. Around 30 patients were treated on the scene for minor injuries, while three were taken to a local hospital.